 <sect1 xml:id="storage.docupdates.sle12_sp1">
  <title>December 2015 (Initial Release of &productname; 12 SP1)</title>
  <!--list of general issues that apply to all books-->
  <xi:include href="common_docupdates_sp1_i.xml"/>
  <variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- 1 Overview of File Systems in Linux  -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.filesystems" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
    <itemizedlist>
     <listitem>
      <para> Mentioned that subvolumes with the option <literal>no copy on
       write</literal> for <filename>/var/lib/mariadb</filename>,
       <filename>/var/lib/pgsql</filename>, and
       <filename>/var/lib/libvirt/images</filename> are created by default to
       avoid extensive fragmenting with Btrfs.</para>
     </listitem>
     <listitem>
       <para>Mentioned compression with Btrf and its implications, see <xref
             linkend="sec.filesystems.major.btrfs.compress"/> (Fate #316463).
       </para>
     </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- 4 LVM Configuration -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.lvm"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Added a tip on the option <option>--resizefs</option> for the commands
	<command>lvextend</command>, <command>lvresize</command>, and
	<command>lvreduce</command> to <xref linkend="sec.lvm.cli.resize"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- 6 Software RAID Configuration -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.raid" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
    <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
     <listitem>
      <para>
       Added <xref linkend="sec.raid.trouble.autorecovery"/> (Fate #316381).
      </para>
     </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- 12 iSNS for Linux -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.isns" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
    <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
     <listitem>
      <para>
       Updated commands to restart iSCSI service and target in <xref
       linkend="sec.isns.domains.iscsi_nodes"/> (Fate #317929).
      </para>
     </listitem>
     <listitem>
       <para>Inserted new section about UNMAP command in <xref
       linkend="sec.iscsi.unmap"/> (Fate #316345).</para>
     </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- 15 Managing Multipath I/O for Devices -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.multipath"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Fixed a wrong command in <xref
	linkend="sec.multipath.best_practice.scanpart"/> (Doc Comment #27121).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Bugfixes</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
	<filename>/var/lib/open-iscsi moved</filename> (<link
	xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=952469"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	KIWI build fails because of noudevsync (<link
	xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=943298"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	VM <literal>volume_list</literal> description error ( <link
	xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=951321"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Removed hint on restriction of 256 logical volumes (only applies to
	lvm1) (<link
	xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=947941"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Replaced <quote>memory space</quote> with <quote>storage space</quote>
	(<link
	xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=948174"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Added a tip on the option <option>--resizefs</option> for LVM resizing
	commands (<link
	xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=947952"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	lvmetad is Enabled by Default on SLE 12 SP1 (<link
	xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=948178"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Corrected LVM introduction (<link
	xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=947949"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Removed a duplicated paragraph on thinly provisioned LVM (<link
	xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=947484"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        <filename>/boot</filename> may reside on RAID 1 in <xref
        linkend="cha.raidroot"/> (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=939197"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Replaced <guimenu>Login</guimenu> with <guimenu>Connect</guimenu> in
        <xref linkend="sec.iscsi.initiator.yast.discovered"/> (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=939529"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	use_lvmetad, Change Does not Describe Required Target Value
        (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=939519"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  </sect1>
  
 <sect1 xml:id="storage.docupdates.sle12_ga_maint1">
  <title>February 2015 (Documentation Maintenance Update)</title>

  <variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>General</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Completely restructured the manual by introducing parts.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Completely revised the complete guide.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Shortened the majority of procedures.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        The <systemitem>cciss</systemitem> driver has been replaced with the
        <systemitem>hpsa</systemitem> driver. Changed all affected
        paragraphs accordingly (Fate #316683).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.filesystems"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.filesystems.major.btrfs.suse"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.filesystems.major.btrfs.quota"/> (Fate
        #315690).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.filesystems.major.btrfs.deduplication"/>
        (Fate #316317).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added ReiserFs to the list of file systems that can be converted to
        Btrfs (Fate #313096).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added a note on the new XFS on-disk format to
        <xref linkend="sec.filesystems.major.prealloc"/> (Fate #317042).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.filesystems.major.ext4"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added a note about the support status of ReiserFs to
        <xref linkend="sec.filesystems.major.reiser"/> (Fate #313799).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.resize_fs"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.resize_fs.usecases"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.resize_fs.btrfs"/> (Fate #310777).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.resize_fs.xfs"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.lvm"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated all parts dealing with the &yast; Partitioner, because of a
        new design and workflow.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added instructions on how to list physical volumes used by logical
        volumes to <xref linkend="sec.lvm.vg_resize"/> (Fate #316074).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.lvm.cli.lvmetad"/> (Fate #314556).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.raid"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated all parts dealing with the &yast; Partitioner, because of a
        new design and workflow.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.raid.yast.names"/> (Fate #315590).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.raid10"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed RAID&nbsp;6 from this chapter, since setting up
        RAID&nbsp;6 arrays is now supported by the &yast; Partitioner.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.raid10.complex"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.isns"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed all discovery domain set stuff, since this is no longer
        supported by open-isns.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.iscsi"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Replaced iSCSI Target with iSCSI LIO Target.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.multipath"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Restructured the whole chapter.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed <literal>prio_callout</literal> from
        <xref linkend="sec.multipath.policies_failover.prio"/>, since it is
        no longer supported.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.multipath.best_practice"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Bugfixes</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Replace ReiserFS by Ext3 for Shrinking LV
        (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=884287"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        System Drops Into Emergency Shell After Enabling Multipath
        (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=889317/"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        There is no iSCSI Target in the Package List
        (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=905239"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </sect1>
